TY  - JOUR
T1  - Bequest as a Public Good within Marriage: A Note
AU  - Zhang, Junsen
Y1  - 1994/02/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/261926
DO  - 10.1086/261926
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 187
EP  - 193
VL  - 102
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - Bequest to and marriage of children can lead to a Pareto-inefficient allocation. The inefficiency (or market failure) arises because one family, making a bequest to its own child, ignores the contribution to the utility of the other family whose child enters the marriage. This note shows that an assortative mating rule based on bequests can improve or even restore Pareto efficiency when parents take account of the rule in deciding the amount of bequests to their own children.
AB  - Bequest to and marriage of children can lead to a Pareto-inefficient allocation. The inefficiency (or market failure) arises because one family, making a bequest to its own child, ignores the contribution to the utility of the other family whose child enters the marriage. This note shows that an assortative mating rule based on bequests can improve or even restore Pareto efficiency when parents take account of the rule in deciding the amount of bequests to their own children.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/261926
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/261926
Y2  - 2024/03/23
ER  - 

